description: OPINION AND ORDER re: 507 MOTION to Dismiss Second Consolidated Amended Class Action Complaint. filed by Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd., Standard Chartered PLC, Morgan Stanley, RBC Capital Markets, LLC, Societe Generale S.A., Morgan Stanley & Co. LLC, Credit Suisse AG, Credit Suisse Securities (USA) LLC, Morgan Stanley & Co. International plc, Deutsche Bank AG, Credit Suisse Group AG. For the foregoing reasons, the NSDs' motion is GRANTED with respect to - Plaintiffs' antitrust claims based on transactions executed on foreign exchanges; - Plaintiffs' antitrust claims based on transactions between U.S.-domiciled OTC Plaintiffs (operating outside the United States) and a foreign desk of a Defendant; - Plaintiffs' claims (antitrust and CEA) based on transactions executed before December 1, 2007; - Exchange Plaintiffs' CEA false reporting claims; and - Exchange Plaintiffs' CEA claims arising out of transactions conducted on foreign exchanges. The motion is DENIED as to all other claims. The Clerk of Court is directed to close the motion at Docket No. 507. (Signed by Judge Lorna G. Schofield on 9/20/2016) (kgo) (Entered: 09/20/2016)
